answers.body_markdown:
You&#39;re *only* `print`ing when your test passes, so any line that doesn&#39;t pass the test doesn&#39;t end up in the new file (`FileInput` with `inplace=True` replaces the original file with whatever you emit to `sys.stdout`; if you don&#39;t emit anything, it doesn&#39;t write anything). If you want the other lines to pass unchanged, you need to output the original line in the `else` case:

    with fileinput.FileInput(bmark_file, inplace=True, backup=&#39;.bak&#39;) as file:
        for line in file :
            unique=&quot;id=&quot;+core
            if unique in line:
                print(line.replace(link[&#39;href&#39;], vboard[core.lower()][&#39;benchmarks.tls&#39;]), end=&#39;&#39;)
            else:
                print(line, end=&#39;&#39;)  # Or just sys.stdout.write(line)

The fact that your file ended up empty implies that the `unique in line` test never passed, so you may be expecting non-existent data.

