I think there are two options for

    &lt;app-mycomp cleanup&gt;&lt;/app-mycomp&gt;


1) The directive knows its host component. So you can inject the host into the constructor

    ...
    constructor(private host: MycompComponent) { }
    ...

2) and if the directive doesn&#39;t know the host. This one is a bit complex
The host component needs to provide itself

    @Component({
      selector: &#39;app-mycomp&#39;,
      templateUrl: &#39;./mycomp.component.html&#39;,
      styleUrls: [&#39;./mycomp.component.css&#39;],
      providers: [{  
        provide: &#39;cleanable&#39;, 
        useExisting: forwardRef(()=&gt; MycompComponent)
      }]
    })
    export class MycompComponent extends Cleanable implements OnInit { ... }

Now you can inject it as well in the directive

    constructor(@Inject(&#39;cleanable&#39;) private host: Cleanable) { ... }

Finally, in the directive you can define the life cycle hooks.

